Results for object placement:
Success rate (higher is better) and average relative pose distance for object placement (at a defined target pose) (lower is better).
Evaluation of the 6D object pose estimation (OPE) of the chosen objects for picking:
Success rate for OPE based on commonly used evaluation metrics (higher is better) and average relative pose distance for OPE (lower is better).
Best results are marked in bold.
